{
  "texts": [
    "The positive training dataset consisted of 2340 (c, g) pairs formed between 1438 compounds and 499 targets.",
    "A total of 5,614,766 (c, g) combinations of the 1438 compounds with genes that are not annotated as targets formed the negative training dataset.",
    "During the training, we randomly sampled 231,660 negative pairs, so that the final training set consists of 1% positive labels and 99% negative labels.",
    "The positive and negative labels made equal contributions to the model training after weighting.",
    "The test dataset consisted of 67,763,724 (c, g) pairs formed between 18,855 compounds and 4784 targets, which included 2433 (c, g) pairs formed by 509 polypharmacological compounds (> 5 targets/compound) and 507 targets."
  ]
}